T1  - Predicting credit spreads
AU  - Krishnan, C.N.V.
AU  - Ritchken, Peter H.
AU  - Thomson, James B.
JO  - Journal of Financial Intermediation
VL  - 19
IS  - 4
SP  - 529
EP  - 563
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/10/01/
SN  - 1042-9573
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jfi.2009.02.004
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1042957309000278
AB  - Predictions of firm-level credit spreads based on the current spot and forward credit spreads can be significantly improved upon by using the information contained in the shape of the credit-spread curve. However, the current credit-spread curve is not a sufficient statistic for predicting future out-of-sample credit spreads; predictions can be significantly improved upon by exploiting the information contained in the shape of the riskless yield curve. In the presence of credit-spread and riskless factors, other macroeconomic, marketwide, and firm-specific risk variables do not significantly improve predictions of credit spreads. These results have important implications for credit-spreads modeling as well as for better understanding corporate capital structure and risk management policies.
